who are giving them their time, thought and brains and influence towards this great effort.

22:35.680 --> 22:40.600
Kristen, Mr. Clayton said you had been up to Canada.

22:40.600 --> 22:43.720
What was your reaction there?

22:43.720 --> 22:45.920
What the Canadians do about it?

22:45.920 --> 22:53.760
Well the Canadian I saw members of the government as well as the various members of the parliamentary

22:53.760 --> 22:59.560
bodies who had been concerned many of the NATO parliamentarians and they would like

22:59.560 --> 23:04.200
to work out a method of representation to set up a commission.

23:04.200 --> 23:10.600
They are very much interested as you know in Canada at the moment there is a really

23:10.600 --> 23:17.640
discussion going on because of the influence at least in some of Mr. McMillan statements

23:17.640 --> 23:24.040
that the British are going to join the common market and Canada naturally wondering as one

23:24.040 --> 23:29.160
of the commonwealth countries what is going to become of the her special privilege is

23:29.160 --> 23:31.840
as a commonwealth country in the British market.

23:31.840 --> 23:38.640
So it's a pretty hot subject but I think that the Canadians all of those that I spoke to

23:38.640 --> 23:44.040
feel that the exploration in which the commissions of this kind might make the other might be

23:44.040 --> 23:45.640
very helpful and very useful.

23:46.280 --> 23:51.000
Well, Kristen, how about Mr. Diffinbacker, the Prime Minister of Canada?

23:51.000 --> 23:54.240
He's been very much interested in hasn't he?

23:54.240 --> 23:58.120
Yes, he's been very much interested but he is very much concerned about this move for

23:58.120 --> 24:02.920
the British at the moment and he is asked for meeting of the Prime Ministers of all the

24:02.920 --> 24:05.120
commonwealth countries to discuss it.

24:05.120 --> 24:08.600
I don't know whether that will come about or not because I know he said the British are

24:08.600 --> 24:14.160
sending very high ranking ministers to those countries now to Australia and New Zealand

24:14.160 --> 24:17.080
and Canada to discuss the relations that come to us.

24:17.080 --> 24:21.080
They're also sending another high commissioner to some of their asianic members of the

24:21.080 --> 24:22.080
commonwealth.

24:22.080 --> 24:26.440
Well, the NATO parliamentarians in Canada have a meeting and take action.

24:26.440 --> 24:27.440
Are you with them?

24:27.440 --> 24:28.440
Yes, they did.

24:28.440 --> 24:31.280
They discussed a thing from beginning to end.

24:31.280 --> 24:37.280
We've been to one hour discussing very phases of it and then they have to resolution favouring

24:37.280 --> 24:38.280
it.

24:38.280 --> 24:45.560
So that Greece, one of our NATO nations has already set up a council or a commission similar

24:45.560 --> 24:46.560
to ours.

24:46.560 --> 24:48.400
How would they Mr. Will?

24:48.400 --> 24:53.560
Yes, and they may say call a Hellenic citizens commission on NATO.

24:53.560 --> 24:59.360
I've always been impressed with the fact that if a military alliance is going to survive

24:59.360 --> 25:05.840
if we're going to have unity and strength that we had to have some better means of political

25:05.840 --> 25:12.160
consultation, not that we follow on another's political policy in every case, but we all

25:12.160 --> 25:15.360
at least each know what the others doing.

25:15.360 --> 25:20.080
Like in the case, you were Secretary of State, I believe, or were you Mr. Herder when the

25:20.080 --> 25:21.880
Suez of Fair came?

25:21.880 --> 25:24.200
I was under Secretary of that time.

25:24.200 --> 25:26.440
You were under Secretary of State.

25:26.440 --> 25:32.120
And the French and British took move and it had not been discussed with the United States

25:32.120 --> 25:35.240
although it involved the whole world.

25:35.240 --> 25:40.600
Is that part of the things that you will be talking about when you meet with these representatives

25:40.600 --> 25:41.600
of other countries?

25:41.600 --> 25:48.200
Well, one of the problems in NATO that has always arisen has been so-called political consultation

25:48.200 --> 25:55.440
that is the effort to try to get a common meeting ground and a common policy.

25:55.440 --> 25:58.600
It improved very, very considerably.

25:58.600 --> 26:08.240
But it is never going to be completely satisfactory in my way of thinking until our political ties

26:08.240 --> 26:10.760
are stronger than the other present times.

26:10.760 --> 26:14.880
And that will be part of the things that you will try to bring about, Mr. Chair.

26:14.880 --> 26:15.880
That's right.

26:15.880 --> 26:21.280
How do you view the General Western Atlantic picture of the present time, Mr. Will?

26:21.280 --> 26:34.240
I think that it illustrates very strongly the need for some means of bringing the Western

26:34.240 --> 26:39.560
of NATO countries and the OECD countries closer together.

26:39.560 --> 26:49.320
If we are to successfully defend ourselves in America against the monolithic power of the

26:49.320 --> 26:56.640
Soviet Union plus Chinese, they have a billion people now which is one out of every three

26:56.640 --> 26:58.480
in the world.

26:58.480 --> 27:05.120
And if it ever should get to be two out of three, I think the world has lost its freedom.

27:05.120 --> 27:12.320
Well, I just want to say all my own ladies and gentlemen that I think are great hope for

27:12.320 --> 27:18.000
pieces in the Atlantic community and free people standing together.

27:18.000 --> 27:24.600
I think that Mr. Clayton and Mr. Header and the others on this commission are rendering

27:24.600 --> 27:29.920
a great public service and trying to bring about ways and means so that we can stand together

27:29.920 --> 27:31.920
well better.

27:31.920 --> 27:33.360
We are indebted to them.

27:33.360 --> 27:37.320
It may make the difference between peace and war in the days to come.

27:37.320 --> 27:41.200
So Mr. Will Clayton, I want to thank you very much for being with us.

27:41.200 --> 27:42.200
Yes.

27:42.200 --> 27:44.840
Because the Commander is all for nicely your coming.

27:44.840 --> 27:46.440
Be with us and we all appreciate it.

27:46.440 --> 27:47.440
That's all for now.

27:47.440 --> 27:48.440
Thank you very much.

