We have been thinking for a long time all of us about how we can have person to person

28:15.320 --> 28:22.600
to contact and the interest to better understanding and eventual peace relations in the world.

28:22.600 --> 28:28.720
In this Congress there was no organization or new plan that started out with more skepticism,

28:28.720 --> 28:35.120
more doubt about it, more an organization and turned out to have general approbation

28:35.120 --> 28:37.240
and approval and peace core.

28:37.240 --> 28:42.240
But we have all heard so much about in which we are so interested in.

28:42.240 --> 28:46.680
We are very honored today to have with us the man who has organized the peace core,

28:46.680 --> 28:51.400
who is its general director, who is giving it a very wonderful direction.

28:51.400 --> 28:58.000
It is taking many nations of the world, sergeant's tribe, sergeant sugar to have you with us

28:58.000 --> 29:04.000
today and to talk to my people in Tennessee and other states that may be listening and watching.

29:04.000 --> 29:05.000
Thank you, Senator.

29:05.000 --> 29:10.600
I am very happy to be here and have this chance to tell the people of Tennessee on your

29:10.600 --> 29:14.520
program something about what the peace core is doing and what it hopes to do.

29:14.520 --> 29:19.160
Before you do that, we all call you sergeant and everybody thinks that you might have been

29:19.160 --> 29:24.720
a sergeant in the army or something, but actually you weren't a sergeant where you were.

29:24.720 --> 29:29.680
No I wasn't, but it just happened to be my name, but I do make the point that sergeant

29:29.680 --> 29:32.400
is the highest rank in the peace core.

29:32.400 --> 29:33.920
We have very few animals around us.

29:33.920 --> 29:37.400
We don't have any generals or admirals, but actually I think you were a lieutenant commander

29:37.400 --> 29:38.640
in the Navy weren't you.

29:38.640 --> 29:39.640
That's right, yes I was.

29:39.640 --> 29:44.600
And I may say, incidentally, a very successful businessman who has given up his business to

29:44.600 --> 29:50.720
devote it to this and very great coves.

29:50.720 --> 29:57.400
Well, sergeant Tennessee has been playing a very important part in the peace core not only

29:57.400 --> 30:03.920
as the daughter of our junior senator, Senator Gore and Nancy, one of your good volunteers

30:03.920 --> 30:05.520
and the very star, isn't it?

30:05.520 --> 30:09.560
That's right, Nancy's worked at our headquarters and the beginning has done a fine job too.

30:09.560 --> 30:15.640
And then I believe Sam Babitt, who is the dean of students at Vanderbilt University,

30:15.640 --> 30:17.480
is part of your organization?

30:17.480 --> 30:21.480
Yes, I'm happy to say he is no longer the dean at Vanderbilt.

30:21.480 --> 30:23.520
He's now working full-time for us.

30:23.520 --> 30:28.120
He had a very successful and distinguished career in that work at Vanderbilt tonight with us.

30:28.120 --> 30:32.880
That's a great loss to Vanderbilt, but it's a great game to you.

30:32.880 --> 30:40.640
Then I believe Dr. Nicholas Hobbs, who was the, or maybe his, the professor of psychology

30:40.640 --> 30:45.680
at P. Barat University, was head of this election group for the peace core was enough.

30:45.680 --> 30:46.680
Yes, that's true, Senator.

30:46.680 --> 30:51.160
And I think Nick Hobbs deserves a great deal of credit for the early success, which the

30:51.160 --> 30:56.960
peace core has gained overseas because the payoff so far as the peace core is concerned

30:56.960 --> 31:01.400
is how well does it do in the foreign country after the volunteers get there?

31:01.400 --> 31:04.360
How well does the volunteers do their job?

31:04.360 --> 31:09.600
And Nick Hobbs was the person responsible for the selection of all of the peace core volunteers

31:09.600 --> 31:11.800
who are overseas now.

31:11.800 --> 31:19.760
And we were talking about the dean of students at Sam Babitt, the dean of students at Vanderbilt

31:19.760 --> 31:20.760
University.

31:20.760 --> 31:21.760
Yes.

31:21.760 --> 31:25.160
Well, we're proud of the part that Tennessee is playing and has played.

31:25.160 --> 31:28.200
Now tell us just what does the peace core do?

31:28.200 --> 31:29.200
What is your plan?

31:29.200 --> 31:30.200
What is your program?

31:30.200 --> 31:31.200
What is your success then?

31:31.200 --> 31:32.200
Yes.

31:32.200 --> 31:36.400
Well, the peace core today is operating in 12 different foreign countries.

31:36.400 --> 31:41.440
Right now we're concentrating in the area of education, in health, in agriculture, and

31:41.440 --> 31:46.480
in the various skilled crafts such as the Carpenters, Laborers, Plumbers, etc.

31:46.480 --> 31:50.640
For the most part, so far, we've concentrated in the education area.

31:50.640 --> 31:55.000
And I include in that all kinds of education, primary education, high school, university

31:55.000 --> 31:59.040
education, agricultural education, home economics, and so on.

31:59.040 --> 32:01.680
It doesn't all just take place in a classroom.

32:01.680 --> 32:05.400
And a person to qualify does not have to be a teacher in the sense that they have a teaching

32:05.400 --> 32:07.280
certificate here in our country.

32:07.280 --> 32:13.440
We've taken a great many bachelor's of arts or bachelor's of science, graduates of good

32:13.440 --> 32:18.200
colleges in our country, and made them into very effective teachers in Africa and South

32:18.200 --> 32:19.600
America and over in Asia.

32:19.600 --> 32:21.640
Well, how are they getting along, Sergeant?

32:21.640 --> 32:24.360
Well, they're getting along wonderfully well so far.

32:24.360 --> 32:29.560
The best indication, Senator, of their success is the fact that every one of the countries

32:29.560 --> 32:34.960
where the peace core is now operating has asked us to double or triple or even quadruple

32:34.960 --> 32:37.960
the number of peace core volunteers in those countries.

32:37.960 --> 32:38.960
Not necessarily.

32:38.960 --> 32:39.960
It's a recommendation now.

32:39.960 --> 32:44.640
Do you go into countries unless they ask you to and unless they welcome you and unless

32:44.640 --> 32:46.280
they cooperate with you?

32:46.280 --> 32:47.280
No, we don't.

32:47.280 --> 32:50.960
We insist in fact that we be invited before we go.

32:50.960 --> 32:55.000
And in a cost-conscious country like ours, I think it's interesting that every one of

32:55.000 --> 33:01.720
the nations has already voluntarily contributed money and services and other goods to the

33:01.720 --> 33:03.320
peace core.

33:03.320 --> 33:07.240
Without us even asking them for it, for example, one country has supplied all the housing.

33:07.240 --> 33:11.640
A large part of the public transportation around in the country that we have to use has

33:11.640 --> 33:13.200
been given to us.

33:13.200 --> 33:17.760
Other forms of equipment, one country in South America has provided almost a million

33:17.760 --> 33:21.920
dollars worth of their equipment to us voluntarily.

33:21.920 --> 33:28.640
Well, I guess, of course, some of these are developing nations and living conditions

33:28.640 --> 33:31.080
might not be very any too pleasant.

33:31.080 --> 33:33.080
They may have many hardships.

33:33.080 --> 33:37.040
Do you have any complaints from the people in the peace core?

33:37.040 --> 33:39.200
Well, we've been lucky so far.

33:39.200 --> 33:43.320
The people who volunteer for the peace core in the first instance are very well motivated,

33:43.320 --> 33:45.560
a highly motivated individuals.

33:45.560 --> 33:49.400
And they know before they go overseas that there are going to be problems and difficulties.

33:49.400 --> 33:50.800
But so far we've been lucky.

33:50.800 --> 33:54.840
For example, in the area of disease, many people thought that there would be a lot of accidents

33:54.840 --> 33:57.600
or disease in many of these countries.

33:57.600 --> 34:01.880
The United States Public Health Service is responsible for the health of the peace core volunteers.

34:01.880 --> 34:07.920
They have told us that they, the public health service, has been surprised at the small

34:07.920 --> 34:10.720
amount of disease which has afflicted the peace core so far.

34:10.720 --> 34:12.840
We're very lucky that one.

34:12.840 --> 34:15.560
How many do you have in the peace core at the present time in massage?

34:15.560 --> 34:22.960
Well, it's changing almost hourly as we make this telecast senator between Thursday of

34:22.960 --> 34:28.440
this week and Monday of next week, 333 new volunteers will go into training with the

34:28.440 --> 34:29.600
peace core.

34:29.600 --> 34:32.800
So as of today, we have about 700 overseas.

34:32.800 --> 34:37.880
We have 200 in training and over this weekend we'll put another 300 in training.

34:37.880 --> 34:41.040
So if you add all that up, it comes with about 1200 people.

34:41.040 --> 34:45.240
And I heard you say somewhere the other day that only less than a half a dozen had asked

34:45.240 --> 34:46.240
to come home.

34:46.240 --> 34:47.240
Is that correct?

34:47.240 --> 34:48.240
That's right.

34:48.240 --> 34:51.280
We've brought four home from overseas.

34:51.280 --> 34:57.480
One was what we call compassionate case because this boy's father died and they get a large

34:57.480 --> 34:58.480
number of brothers and sisters.

34:58.480 --> 35:01.240
His mother needed him back to help support the family.

35:01.240 --> 35:04.440
Another one was the famous postal card girl from Nigeria.

35:04.440 --> 35:07.640
The girl wrote the postal card and creates such a ruckus at that time.

35:07.640 --> 35:09.280
Yes, she was a very fine girl, too.

35:09.280 --> 35:10.280
I'm sure.

35:10.280 --> 35:14.840
She was a magnum, a comalaud graduate of Smith College incidentally.

35:14.840 --> 35:17.880
She had been trained at Harvard and she's still working for the peace core.

35:17.880 --> 35:22.040
I'm happy to say she's in our Washington headquarters and in June, I think it is going to be

35:22.040 --> 35:24.960
married and perhaps you'll be able to continue to work for it.

35:24.960 --> 35:28.440
When I say you have a lot of volunteers, it doesn't mean that anyone who volunteers can

35:28.440 --> 35:29.440
get in does it?

35:29.440 --> 35:30.440
It does.

35:30.440 --> 35:31.440
No, it doesn't.

35:31.440 --> 35:35.440
So we're getting new volunteers now at the rate of 2000 a month.

35:35.440 --> 35:39.880
So we expect that between January and June, for example, about 12,000 people will volunteer

35:39.880 --> 35:41.160
for the peace core.

35:41.160 --> 35:44.280
We probably won't take more than 3,000 of those.

35:44.280 --> 35:49.320
So about one out of every four or one out of every five applicants gets in.

35:49.320 --> 35:54.520
Are they mostly college graduates or young people or what kind of people are?

35:54.520 --> 35:57.200
About 80% are college graduates now.

35:57.200 --> 36:01.320
But we hope that many more people who do not have a college degree will volunteer for

36:01.320 --> 36:03.000
the peace core.

36:03.000 --> 36:09.440
Countries overseas need skilled craftsmen, construction people, automacanics, diesel engineers, nurses,

36:09.440 --> 36:13.720
job laboratory technicians, practical nurses and so on.

36:13.720 --> 36:15.600
And many of these people don't have college degrees.

36:15.600 --> 36:17.640
They don't need to have a college degree.

36:17.640 --> 36:19.760
What's more, they don't have to speak the language.

36:19.760 --> 36:20.760
We teach them the language.

36:20.760 --> 36:24.880
I'll go ask you what kind of training do they have before they go and say they're going

36:24.880 --> 36:30.520
to some nation and Africa, South America, Asia, what kind of training do they have?

36:30.520 --> 36:37.600
Well, they get, I think, a really rare type of training in that we give training in the

36:37.600 --> 36:41.240
culture, customs and traditions of the foreign country to which they're going.

36:41.240 --> 36:42.400
We train in the language.

36:42.400 --> 36:46.000
We teach them about American history and government and politics.

36:46.000 --> 36:47.440
We give them physical education.

36:47.440 --> 36:49.240
We give them health education.

36:49.240 --> 36:53.200
So that when they arrive in the foreign country, they arrive there knowing the history and

36:53.200 --> 36:54.360
the culture of that country.

36:54.360 --> 36:56.320
They know the language of the country.

36:56.320 --> 37:00.120
And the job that they're going to do in that country has already been selected for

37:00.120 --> 37:01.120
them.

37:01.120 --> 37:05.360
They know what kind of work they're going to do and they've been prepared to do that work.

37:05.360 --> 37:09.480
So I started so often in connection with our diplomats and it may not be justified.

37:09.480 --> 37:14.560
There's a complaint that they live to themselves and they have big capitals of the city of

37:14.560 --> 37:17.080
the countries they go to.

37:17.080 --> 37:18.600
How about the members of the Peace Corps?

37:18.600 --> 37:23.320
Did they get out and mix and live with the people and get to know them and work with

37:23.320 --> 37:24.320
them directly?

37:24.320 --> 37:28.880
Well, Senator, that is one of the basic requirements of the Peace Corps, namely that our personnel

37:28.880 --> 37:34.920
live with the natives or the citizens of the foreign country that they're living in.

37:34.920 --> 37:41.880
But I'd say 85% of all Peace Corps volunteers live outside of the capital cities.

37:41.880 --> 37:45.520
The only ones who live in a capital city are people who are teaching, for example, in

37:45.520 --> 37:47.960
a big university in the capital city.

37:47.960 --> 37:52.200
In Bangkok, the big university, as you all know, is called Kula Long Court University.

37:52.200 --> 37:55.440
We have 10 men on the faculty of that university.

37:55.440 --> 38:00.000
So they do live in Bangkok, but most, by far, the great majority, maybe 80 to 90% of our

38:00.000 --> 38:03.000
people live in the rural communities of various countries.

38:03.000 --> 38:08.000
Of course, ours, the Peace Corps has only been going for just a few months, but from

38:08.000 --> 38:13.080
people coming from countries where Peace Corps has been operating, it seems to me that it's

38:13.080 --> 38:18.600
already paying great dividends, but it's been your experience of what's your report.

38:18.600 --> 38:22.980
Well, we agree that some of the most encouraging things have been articles written on the Peace

38:22.980 --> 38:28.520
Corps by foreign journalists and by foreign celebrities, even like Arnold Toyne, be the famous

38:28.520 --> 38:32.800
British historian, voluntarily wrote an article for the London Times, which was printed

38:32.800 --> 38:38.040
all over the world, commending the Peace Corps and telling about the volunteers that he had

38:38.040 --> 38:39.040
seen.

38:39.040 --> 38:44.560
The Associated Press, the United Press, the British news gathering agency called Reuters.

38:44.560 --> 38:48.760
All of these people have interviewed the Peace Corps and have talked to experts about the

38:48.760 --> 38:50.320
Peace Corps in foreign countries.

38:50.320 --> 38:55.520
We have no way of controlling what they publish or say, and uniformly so far, the reports

38:55.520 --> 39:02.240
by these nonpartisan third party groups have been favorable to our operations.

39:02.240 --> 39:06.440
I know that the Peace Corps goes to a lot of neutral countries and a lot of newly developing

39:06.440 --> 39:07.440
countries.

39:07.440 --> 39:12.520
On stand you have a number of Peace Corps people in the Philippines, which is a friendly

39:12.520 --> 39:13.520
nation.

39:13.520 --> 39:16.960
Why would you send Peace Corps representatives to a friendly nation?

39:16.960 --> 39:22.120
Well, maybe I'm all fashion, but I believe in making better friends of the friends you

39:22.120 --> 39:23.120
already have.

39:23.120 --> 39:24.920
I agree with you very thoroughly.

39:24.920 --> 39:29.840
There are things to be sort of a tendency in some quarters to think that you only do business

39:29.840 --> 39:34.760
with people that you might lose, that the neutral nations, the so-called neutral nations,

39:34.760 --> 39:36.720
are the ones that you should curry favor with.

39:36.720 --> 39:39.800
Well, I'm in favor of working with the neutral nations.

39:39.800 --> 39:43.920
We have people in Ghana and other neutral nations, but still in all, I think that when a country

39:43.920 --> 39:49.280
has proven its friendship for us, they're trying to follow the democratic free way of life

39:49.280 --> 39:52.040
and to have trade with us and so on, that we should try to help them too.

39:52.040 --> 39:56.280
And the Philippines is an outstanding example and the Pacific of this type of favorable

39:56.280 --> 39:57.800
country, favorable to ours.

39:57.800 --> 40:03.240
I heard you say where they had 45 different languages or dialects and that they're all

40:03.240 --> 40:04.240
being told English.

40:04.240 --> 40:05.240
Is that so?

40:05.240 --> 40:06.240
Yeah, that's true.

40:06.240 --> 40:10.280
Because in the Philippines, one of the essential ingredients for keeping those islands

40:10.280 --> 40:14.600
together as a nation is that they have a common language and the only language they have

40:14.600 --> 40:16.440
in common now is English.

40:16.440 --> 40:20.880
Also, we've often heard and talked about the fact that Philippines should be a symbol

40:20.880 --> 40:23.320
in the far east of democracy at work.

40:23.320 --> 40:26.960
But we forget sometimes that the only way that the Philippines can communicate with the

40:26.960 --> 40:29.880
rest of the Asia, a rest of Asia, is in English.

40:29.880 --> 40:33.120
If they don't know English, they can't talk to the people who live in Thailand or even

40:33.120 --> 40:34.120
up in Formosa.

40:34.120 --> 40:36.120
So, English is essential as well.

40:36.120 --> 40:38.920
And it's been wonderfully accepted in the Philippines, is that not true?

40:38.920 --> 40:39.920
Yes, that's true.

40:39.920 --> 40:41.840
Well, what are the communists there, that peace corps?

40:41.840 --> 40:43.320
What's their reaction?

40:43.320 --> 40:49.680
Well, it just happens that yesterday I got a new publication issued and printed in China.

40:49.680 --> 40:54.120
It has mailed, say, Tongs picture on the cover and it's distributed all over the world.

40:54.120 --> 40:57.840
This particular copy happened to be picked up in Africa and it was a long article in

40:57.840 --> 41:03.160
there blasting the Peace Corps saying that we were a tool of imperialist aggression, that

41:03.160 --> 41:07.200
we were a nest of spies, that we were out to subvert the people's liberties all over

41:07.200 --> 41:08.200
the world.

41:08.200 --> 41:12.400
And it was indicative to us at any rate that the communists don't like the Peace Corps.

41:12.400 --> 41:14.800
Now, if they don't like the Peace Corps, I'm pleased.

41:14.800 --> 41:17.400
That's a good sign you're doing a lot of good.

41:17.400 --> 41:20.520
Well, how much is the Peace Corps costing this year, for instance?

41:20.520 --> 41:25.280
Well, the Congress gave us $30 million as senators, you remember, and that will be enough

41:25.280 --> 41:29.960
to operate us through the first year and to bring about 5,000 Americans into Peace Corps

41:29.960 --> 41:30.960
service.

41:30.960 --> 41:35.920
Right now, we're asking for another $30 million in addition to the first one to bring

41:35.920 --> 41:38.120
in an additional 5,000 people.

41:38.120 --> 41:41.560
And we've been very much encouraged because the committees here on the Hill have supported

41:41.560 --> 41:43.080
our requests so far.

41:43.080 --> 41:44.800
Liberals as well as reactionaries.

41:44.800 --> 41:47.720
Well, I wish we could go on, but that's all the time we have.

41:47.720 --> 41:52.800
I want to thank you for Sergeant Striver for telling us all about the Peace Corps.

41:52.800 --> 41:54.800
That's all until next time, ladies and gentlemen.

41:54.800 --> 41:55.600
Thank you very much.

